VALUES ('ICC:CBC_Chapter11A_11B:2025:CA:11B-703.8.4', '11B-703.8.4', 'Character height.', 'The uppercase letter “I” shall be used to determine the allowable height of all low resolution VMS characters of a font. Viewing distance shall be measured as the horizontal distance between the character and an obstruction preventing further approach towards the sign. The uppercase letter “I” of the font shall have a minimum height complying with Table 11B-703.8.4.

